Usage: source utils
Helper functions for the lib

This script needs to be sourced to work properly
The avaliable functions are listed below

set-args {ARG1} [ARG2] ... [ARGN]
    Creates a json object using environment
    variables as key and values
        ARGs: {KEY}:[VAR]:[RAW]
            KEY: A json key
            VAR: A environment variable, KEY if empty
            RAW: Empty for string, @ for raw json

get-args {ARG1} [ARG2] ... [ARGN]
    Returns an evaluable string of the keys
    and values from JSON keys
        ARGs: {KEY}:[VAR]:[RAW]
            KEY: A json key
            VAR: A environment variable, KEY if empty
            RAW: Empty for string, @ for raw json

format-args {FORMAT} {ARGS} {EXTRA}
    Filter unwanted args from STDIN and
    returns only the specified to STDOUT
        FORMAT: Output format, 'json' or 'url'
        ARGS: Args separated by comma
        EXTRA: A extra jq query

urify {KEY}
    Opens the filepath on a JSON value, and converts
    it to a URI scheme. Accepts a JSON string on STDIN
        KEY: A json key where the filepath is
